President Trump and Prime Minister Khan of Pakistan met at the Davos Congress Centre in Switzerland to discuss trade, Afghanistan, and the issue of Kashmir. President Trump expressed his willingness to help resolve the situation in Kashmir and spoke about the close relationship between the US and Pakistan. Prime Minister Khan highlighted the importance of the US playing a role in resolving the issue with India. President Trump also mentioned the possibility of imposing auto tariffs on imports from Europe if a deal cannot be made. He emphasized the need for fair trade and highlighted the US's disproportionate spending on NATO.